Comments:       first you'll need raw 16 bit mono drum samples in your current directory.
                you can make your own or obtain some from the src pkg @ the url above
                or in the src's distributed by tinycore.
		then you enter into stdin text of this format:                                                                       
		(you can type directly after starting or use jdkdrum <somefile.txt

                <tempo>                                                               
                <instrument> <pattern>                                                
                <instrument> <pattern>                                                
                .                                                                     

                once you enter the final '.', the pattern you entered will play

		example:
		85                                                                             
		kick3   4...4...4...4...                                                       
		kick2   .34..34..34..345                                                       
		clap    7.469.347.469.34                                                       
